1.title: Krystal/Craig vs. Michelle/Jason
1.plot: Competing couples take on two DIY home makeover challenges, without any outside help, for a chance to win $10,000 dollars. Krystal and Craig use a bold color palette in their living room that leaves the judges guessing. Michelle and Jason hope that their attempt at a never-before-seen DIY project pays off.

2.title: Anna Rose/Matt vs. Portia/Errol
2.plot: Competing couples take on two DIY home makeover challenges, without any outside help, for a chance to win $10,000 dollars. Portia and Errol hope their chances of winning aren't in jeopardy after breaking a major rule of the competition. Anna Rose and Matt attempt a stencil wall design that goes horribly wrong.

3.title: Nikki/Mac vs. Lisa/Nick
3.plot: Lisa worries that Nick's perfectionism will prevent them from finishing built-in bookshelves. Nikki and Mac choose a Hollywood Regency theme for their living room, but will the judges think they went too far? Competing couples take on two DIY home makeover challenges, without any outside help, for a chance to win $10,000 dollars.

4.title: Eva/Ian vs. Roshawnda/Chelsea
4.plot: Eva and Ian have to consider abandoning one of their three major carpentry projects when time runs out. Roshawnda and Chelsea use old books to create a custom headboard. Competing couples take on two DIY home makeover challenges, without any outside help, for a chance to win $10,000 dollars.

5.title: Carey/Jeremy vs. Michelle/Jonathan
5.plot: Competing couples take on two DIY home makeover challenges, without any outside help, for a chance to win $10,000 dollars. Carey and Jeremy require two days to resurface a wall with reclaimed wood. Michelle and Jonathan hope that converting an old suitcase into a chair will impress the judges.
